name: One Fall Canyon
description:
Introduction

This canyon is mainly a hike and the dryfalls are climbable, so it would not be considered a technical canyon by most in the canyoneering world. I put it here for reference and beta if anyone is wondering what is up there from the road down below. Basically, not much, or worthy. But it might be worthy to people who want an easy day and hike through a DV canyon.

Approach

Descent

There is a dryfall, about 30 feet high, that can be climbed, or as a rappel if anyone thought they didn't like the exposure

Exit

Red tape
